<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880907-0131 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business: Harken Oil andamp; Gas Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> HOGI </CO><TEXT>   HARKEN OIL andamp; GAS Inc. said it raised $25 million through a private placement of 2.5 million new 12% convertible, cumulative preferred shares. The Bedford, Texas, oil and gas concern said the shares were sold to Dreyfus Convertible Fund and three major Harken shareholders, Traco International N.V., Aeneas Venture Corp. and other affiliates of Harvard University, and Intercontinental Mining andamp; Resources Ltd. Harken said proceeds will be used to fund its purchase of about 35% of Crystal Oil Co. of Shreveport, La., for an estimated $15 million to $18 million and for other acquisitions. Stephens Inc. helped with the placement, Harken said. </TEXT></DOC>